OL,3,CDisruptive pupils' parents should be
OL,4,Cforced to co-operate with schools `
OL,5,Creport
OL,7,FThe Government should make fixing the
OL,8,Fbehaviour crisis in schools an "urgent
OL,9,Fpriority", the paper from the former
OL,10,FLabour prime minister's think tank
OL,11,Fsaid.
OL,13,FThe report said: "Schools should be
OL,14,Fgiven the power to compel families to
OL,15,Fcome to the table and agree an action
OL,16,Fplan when a pupil's behaviour becomes
OL,17,Fseverely disruptive.
OL,19,F"Where families refuse to engage,
OL,20,Fteachers need to be dealt a stronger
OL,21,Fhand.
