OL,3,CDisruptive pupils' parents should be
OL,4,Cforced to co-operate with schools `
OL,5,Creport
OL,7,F"If parents fail to attend
OL,8,Fdisciplinary meetings or engage with
OL,9,Fan action plan, schools should be able
OL,10,Fto escalate concerns to other relevant
OL,11,Fagencies on safeguarding grounds.
OL,13,F"The Government should consider if any
OL,14,Flegal powers similar to those used to
OL,15,Faddress repeated absence without a
OL,16,Fgood reason should apply when parents
OL,17,Frefuse to co-operate repeatedly and
OL,18,Fwithout substantive grounds.
