OL,4,Cforced to co-operate with schools `
OL,5,Creport
OL,7,FHe added: "The idea of giving teachers
OL,8,Fa statutory authority to force parents
OL,9,Fto engage is certainly novel, but we
OL,10,Fwould be concerned that such a policy
OL,11,Fwould create a significant additional
OL,12,Fburden on schools and exacerbate
OL,13,Ftensions with parents.
OL,15,F"Instead, we need to be looking to
OL,16,Fcreate conditions that allow schools
OL,17,Fto work together constructively with
OL,18,Fparents, as well as external agencies
OL,19,Fwhere necessary, in the best interests
OL,20,Fof children and young people."
